WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.733
What abilities does

00:00:02.733 --> 00:00:04.200
a qualified cosmetics formulator

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:04.900
need

00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:05.666
? Why

00:00:05.666 --> 00:00:07.533
arm strength ? Because I'm about to fly

00:00:07.533 --> 00:00:08.833
to France

00:00:08.833 --> 00:00:12.233
to bring back my 10-pound new raw material.

00:00:12.233 --> 00:00:13.733
What's going on?

00:00:13.733 --> 00:00:14.700
In April,

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:15.700
didn't I go to the Netherlands

00:00:15.700 --> 00:00:17.933
to attend the cosmetics exhibition?

00:00:17.933 --> 00:00:19.233
In this video,

00:00:19.233 --> 00:00:21.000
I introduced a new ingredient

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:22.833
that's good for dandruff.

00:00:22.833 --> 00:00:25.666
Later, through laboratory evaluation, I found that

00:00:25.666 --> 00:00:28.933
it was also very effective for closed comedones and acne

00:00:28.933 --> 00:00:30.433
, so I planned to

00:00:30.433 --> 00:00:33.600
use it in the formula of my newly developed cosmetics.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:34.933
What a great thing, right?

00:00:34.933 --> 00:00:37.033
But it's out of stock.

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:38.200
The raw material manufacturer

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:39.333
was quite happy.

00:00:39.333 --> 00:00:41.400
He said that thanks to my previous videos,

00:00:41.400 --> 00:00:44.633
many product managers in the industry have taken a fancy to him.

00:00:44.733 --> 00:00:47.000
The samples were all taken up,

00:00:47.066 --> 00:00:49.433
so I have to fly over

00:00:49.433 --> 00:00:52.600
and bring it back myself.

00:00:59.700 --> 00:01:01.833
Hi everyone, I'm the formulator Xingxing.

00:01:01.833 --> 00:01:03.600
I'm in France now.

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:04.133
Today,

00:01:04.133 --> 00:01:07.000
I'd like you to accompany me to pick up the raw materials. The factory

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:08.233
is called Givaudan

00:01:08.233 --> 00:01:09.600
, which

00:01:10.100 --> 00:01:10.900
you may not

00:01:10.900 --> 00:01:12.433
know . I know what it is

00:01:12.433 --> 00:01:14.000
, but when it comes to perfume

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.033
, among all the world-famous perfumes,

00:01:17.066 --> 00:01:19.333
you can recognize at least one.

00:01:19.333 --> 00:01:22.266
They are all Givaudan products.

00:01:27.033 --> 00:01:29.633
However, this company, ranked among the top three in the industry

00:01:29.633 --> 00:01:32.400
, has a business scope far more than that.

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:33.866
We are about to go

00:01:33.866 --> 00:01:36.300
to its Life Science and Testing Center

00:01:36.300 --> 00:01:38.233
near Reims, France .

00:01:38.233 --> 00:01:39.666
They told me that

00:01:39.666 --> 00:01:41.466
my raw materials are here.

00:01:42.333 --> 00:01:43.333
Oh, it's so windy,

00:01:58.433 --> 00:01:59.400
my raw materials are

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.700
in the building opposite .

00:02:00.700 --> 00:02:02.000
Because it is a research and development center

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:03.233
, I have to

00:02:03.233 --> 00:02:04.900
change clothes before entering.

00:02:04.933 --> 00:02:07.466
They didn't let me wait in the conference room,

00:02:07.466 --> 00:02:09.400
but in the laboratory.

00:02:15.933 --> 00:02:17.500
The raw material I came to pick up this time

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:18.733
is called DandErase™

00:02:18.733 --> 00:02:21.866
, which is a natural raw material for a series of problems

00:02:21.866 --> 00:02:23.233
caused by Malassezia, such as seborrheic dermatitis,

00:02:23.233 --> 00:02:25.600
dandruff, closed comedones, etc. Because the

00:02:25.733 --> 00:02:26.733
cosmetics industry

00:02:26.733 --> 00:02:27.600
has always

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:31.100
used chemically synthesized ingredients like OCT

00:02:31.100 --> 00:02:33.433
to deal with Malassezia infections,

00:02:33.433 --> 00:02:34.933
so if a natural raw material

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.533
can achieve such good data and effects,

00:02:37.533 --> 00:02:39.300
I must have a good chat with them. Now

00:02:39.300 --> 00:02:40.533
that we've caught the expert,

00:02:40.533 --> 00:02:42.600
let's quickly ask a few crucial questions.

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:45.133
I know our raw material is excellent

00:02:45.133 --> 00:02:48.433
, so I use it

00:02:48.433 --> 00:02:49.433
in my new acne-removing product.

00:02:49.433 --> 00:02:51.600
But I'm actually very curious about

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:53.500
how we came up with the idea

00:02:53.600 --> 00:02:56.666
that saffron contains such an ingredient.

00:02:56.666 --> 00:02:57.800
Did we screen it,

00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:00.333
or did we already have some logic

00:03:00.333 --> 00:03:02.000
and deduced it?

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:08.500
We have been researching this topic for more than 10 years

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:10.900
with the goal of finding a

00:03:10.900 --> 00:03:16.000
natural ingredient that is at least as effective as the chemical reference substance on the market.

00:03:16.233 --> 00:03:17.833
So we did it.

00:03:17.833 --> 00:03:21.633
We went through a long screening process

00:03:21.633 --> 00:03:24.966
with the goal of finding a biologically active molecule,

00:03:24.966 --> 00:03:27.066
and we found saffron . Givaudan

00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:28.900
has spent more than a decade

00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.866
on this matter

00:03:31.033 --> 00:03:33.733
, screening thousands of raw materials,

00:03:34.133 --> 00:03:36.100
and finally the hard work paid off.

00:03:36.266 --> 00:03:39.400
Saffron is the raw material for DandErase™. It is an ingredient

00:03:39.433 --> 00:03:41.833
that specifically inhibits the harmful bacteria Malassezia

00:03:42.166 --> 00:03:45.733
through microecological regulation,

00:03:45.733 --> 00:03:46.466
while

00:03:46.466 --> 00:03:49.266
not harming other beneficial bacteria

00:03:49.533 --> 00:03:50.800
. Leah told me that

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:52.433
it felt fateful that

00:03:52.633 --> 00:03:55.033
saffron, as red gold

00:03:55.033 --> 00:03:58.033
, is itself very symbolic.

00:03:58.033 --> 00:04:00.433
It represents healing and vitality,

00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:04.200
so it felt quite fateful

00:04:04.433 --> 00:04:06.066
that we finally found it to be effective against Malassezia.

00:04:06.666 --> 00:04:10.233
So how did we prove its efficacy?

00:04:10.833 --> 00:04:12.200
Let me show you.

00:04:12.533 --> 00:04:15.233
Therefore, inhibiting the growth of Malassezia

00:04:15.233 --> 00:04:17.733
involves different mechanisms.

00:04:17.733 --> 00:04:19.533
With so many bacterial species,

00:04:19.533 --> 00:04:22.633
we can specifically target two of them (pathogenic bacteria)

00:04:22.633 --> 00:04:26.266
without interfering with the rest of the ecosystem (other resident bacteria)

00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:29.766
, thereby not disrupting the healthy environment of the scalp.

00:04:29.866 --> 00:04:31.500
What's more ,

00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:32.700
in clinical tests,

00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:36.033
we achieved a 100% effective effect,

00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:39.433
with no rebound even after discontinuation for a period of time.

00:04:40.033 --> 00:04:42.400
So how many people did we use

00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:44.466
in this clinical trial ?

00:04:44.466 --> 00:04:46.133
Over a hundred volunteers

00:04:46.133 --> 00:04:47.300
. So many

00:04:47.300 --> 00:04:49.333
tips: Most skincare products only require 30 people for "market approval" clinical testing.

00:04:49.333 --> 00:04:52.000
Although ordinary users may not feel it , upstream raw material suppliers

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.900
with a large variety of ingredients

00:04:53.900 --> 00:04:55.533
are good at this. It's not easy

00:04:55.533 --> 00:04:57.933
 

00:04:57.933 --> 00:04:59.300
to organize so many people

00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:01.266
and invest so much clinical funds in

00:05:01.266 --> 00:05:03.333
the research and development of each raw material.

00:05:03.566 --> 00:05:05.133
But as the conversation deepened,

00:05:05.133 --> 00:05:07.033
I felt less surprised.

00:05:07.200 --> 00:05:08.033
Because Givaudan

00:05:08.033 --> 00:05:10.633
has a very complete scientific research management system

00:05:10.633 --> 00:05:12.533
and very professional scientific researchers.

00:05:12.833 --> 00:05:15.433
They even provide a lot of formula guidance

00:05:15.433 --> 00:05:17.433
for downstream product development,

00:05:17.433 --> 00:05:19.666
telling formulators like me

00:05:19.666 --> 00:05:21.733
how to use their raw materials.

00:05:21.900 --> 00:05:22.866
I know that

00:05:22.866 --> 00:05:24.933
we actually have a series of

00:05:24.933 --> 00:05:27.900
hyaluronic acid called needle-free injection.

00:05:27.900 --> 00:05:29.800
Since it is needle-free injection

00:05:29.800 --> 00:05:31.400
, it means it is absorbable.

00:05:31.400 --> 00:05:34.300
How do we prove its absorbability?

00:05:34.600 --> 00:05:35.233
I think you are referring to

00:05:35.233 --> 00:05:37.566
PrimalHyal™ Ultrafiller.

00:05:37.566 --> 00:05:42.433
We precisely design hyaluronic acid and then graft it

00:05:42.433 --> 00:05:45.366
to allow it to penetrate deeper.

00:05:45.366 --> 00:05:46.433
Julia told me

00:05:46.433 --> 00:05:47.733
that they

00:05:47.733 --> 00:05:51.133
have been working with We are collaborating with experts in Raman spectroscopy.

00:05:51.133 --> 00:05:52.100
Raman spectroscopy

00:05:52.100 --> 00:05:55.200
is a fingerprint-like technique

00:05:55.200 --> 00:05:56.266
that can monitor

00:05:56.266 --> 00:05:59.733
the penetration and absorption of ingredients into the skin

00:05:59.733 --> 00:06:02.000
. Givaudan has been using

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:03.700
this cutting-edge detection technology

00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:05.833
to verify ingredient absorption

00:06:08.033 --> 00:06:11.100
. In a rural area surrounded by farmland in France,

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:13.333
this leading biotechnology company

00:06:13.333 --> 00:06:15.300
is secluded,

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:16.200
with scientists

00:06:16.200 --> 00:06:19.466
dedicated to finding more keys to beauty.

00:06:19.466 --> 00:06:23.066
An impromptu, self-service package tour

00:06:23.066 --> 00:06:24.166
allowed me to connect

00:06:24.166 --> 00:06:28.366
with friends who are also dedicated their lives to research.

00:06:28.366 --> 00:06:31.066
It will also be an opportunity for you to see

00:06:31.066 --> 00:06:34.733
that cosmetics are no longer just a chemical industry

00:06:34.733 --> 00:06:37.733
, but a part of life science.

00:06:41.233 --> 00:06:42.266
Oh, baby,

00:06:42.266 --> 00:06:43.433
I have to hold on tight

00:06:43.433 --> 00:06:45.900
, don't let anyone else snatch

00:06:45.900 --> 00:06:48.000
it away! Here's the raw material from the plane.

00:06:48.433 --> 00:06:52.033
A leading global flavor and fragrance company, specializing in flavor and health, as well as fragrance and beauty, is the "mastermind" behind many world-renowned perfumes.

00:06:52.033 --> 00:06:55.466
The active ingredient extracted from saffron has a targeted inhibitory effect on Malassezia fungus, while not affecting other microbial flora, regulating the skin's microecology.

00:06:55.566 --> 00:06:59.066
It is a unique hyaluronic acid derivative designed to provide a cosmetic alternative to injectable fillers. It penetrates twice as deep into the skin as standard hyaluronic acid and is resistant to hyaluronidase, extending its lifespan in the skin.

00:06:59.166 --> 00:07:02.533
Raman spectroscopy is a technique that uses lasers to illuminate a substance and then analyzes changes in the scattered light to reveal the molecular structure and composition. Because different molecules have unique "fingerprint peaks" in the Raman spectrum, detecting these characteristic peaks on the skin can prove that the substance has penetrated, how deep it has penetrated, and ultimately simulate the absorption distribution spectrum

